description:
Flatted Fifth has been playing music together since 2005. The band consists of:
Victor "Voz" Wright: Rhythm Guitar/Lead Vocals
Andrew "Blue" Sheets: Lead Guitar/Vocals
Ryan Heimbach: Bass/Vocals
Seth Heimbach: Drums

Their music could be described as a mix between Stoner Metal, Blues Rock and Jam. Flatted Fifth has a following of loyal fans and are well received at most types of events, although they prefer more adult-oriented venues. They offer and take pride in their original music, but also try to play covers that are outside the bounds of what is normally heard.

In 2008 they released their EP "Nobody Nose" with great praise and was even featured in the jukebox of the historic Lew Wallace Tavern. They have also been featured guests on Thunder 103.9's segment Voice of the Independent Artist.
